It was way beyond the worst experience for a holiday. 
Thanks @Airbnb!!

you pay for the place, waiting for hosts' approval. you are already in the country, tired as hell and have plans for the day. after an hour @Airbnb support tells you, for the place you picked you can get difference back as compensation, if you use given code â¬‡ï¸

when host cancels your booking, @Airbnb support says your payment will be reverted in around 2 weeks. Now we have some amount locked in somewhere. Then @Airbnb support gives you suggestions you can pick, so you are picking one you can manage â¬‡ï¸

you make a plan more than a week ahead, you pay for the place to secure. when arrive to a country you never been before, for a reason your host cancels your booking. might happen right? but the nightmare starts after â¬‡ï¸
I had the worst life experience today using @Airbnb. If such a company is not able keep your back when your host cancels your request on last minute. Then it's not a big company, it is a big joke!
